{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Fluid Sim 2D",
  "description": "Density-displacement particle compute fluid simulation — atom-decomposed from the bundled `fluid_seed` + `fluid_simulate` + `fluid_gradient_rotate` primitives into the curated library.\n\nPer-frame pipeline:\n1. **Seed branch** (open family — pattern math is JSON-editable WGSL): `wgsl_compute(seed_pattern_density)` writes a single-channel density Texture2D selecting one of 7 patterns (cluster / h-lines / v-lines / rings / cross / spiral / edge-ring) via `pattern` uniform. `seed_particles_from_texture` rejection-samples that density into an Array<Particle>. Output flows into `array_feedback.seed`.\n2. **Particle loop** (closes via state, no graph cycle): `array_feedback` holds last frame's sim state, emits as `out`. On `reset_trigger` integer-edge (gated by clip_trigger AND mode==3), reloads from the seed input — the graph-level clear+reseed shape.\n3. **Force-field assembly** (texture-domain math through atoms): `density → gradient_central_diff(scale=UV, wrap=Repeat) → scale_offset_texture(slope_strength * area_scale) → rotate_vec2_by_angle(angle)` replaces the legacy fused gradient/rotate dispatch. `→ gaussian_blur H/V → blurred_force_field`. `radial_burst_force_field` is realised per-particle via `apply_radial_burst_to_particles` downstream.\n4. **Per-particle dispatch chain**: `sample_texture_at_particles(particles, blurred_field) → forces` → `simplex_noise_force_at_particles(forces, particles, amplitude_modulator=blurred_density, amplitude=turbulence_base × turbulence_burst)` (density-adaptive 2D simplex noise added in place to the force buffer — replaces the legacy per-pixel noise advection chain) → `anti_clump_particles(particles, strength_modulator=blurred_density, strength=anti_clump_slider)` (modulator-weighted Brownian kick) → `euler_step_particles(particles, forces, speed)` (frame-rate-normalised step) → `wrap_particles_torus(particles)` (cyclic boundary) → `apply_radial_burst_to_particles` (mode-4 inject).\n5. **Splat**: `scatter_particles → resolve_accumulator → density` (full-res for display, fed back through downsample+blur for the next-frame force-field assembly).\n6. **Display**: `density → reinhard_tone_map (intensity = area_scale × 3) → affine_transform (uv_scale = 1/scale) → final_output`.\n\nClip-trigger modes (same outer-card surface as legacy):\n- mode 0 (Turbulence): boosts the per-particle simplex noise amplitude — `turbulence_base *= 1 + 9*env`. Restores the legacy mode-0 behaviour now that the per-particle noise atom is back in the pipeline.\n- mode 1 (Rot Flip): `rotation_angle += π * env`\n- mode 2 (Flow Inv): `slope_strength *= 1 - 2*env`\n- mode 3 (Pattern): `array_feedback.reset_trigger` edges on clip_trigger AND mode==3 — clear and reseed from the (newly cycled) pattern density texture\n- mode 4 (Inject): `inject_burst` 0.5s state machine drives `apply_radial_burst_to_particles` (point, force, envelope, phase)\n\nKnown parity deltas vs legacy:\n(1) Seed patterns are produced as density textures rejection-sampled by `seed_particles_from_texture` rather than per-particle pattern placement. Particles concentrate in bright regions of the density rather than landing on exact pattern coordinates — visually similar but statistically distributed.\n(2) `visible_count`/excess-particle dead-at-center behaviour is dropped; `fill` slider now multiplies `count_m` to scale `active_count`. Fewer alive particles ↔ smaller buffer ↔ less GPU work.\n(3) Mode-3 pattern cycle still advances on every trigger regardless of mode (legacy did this too).\n(4) Injection burst is applied per-particle post-integration via `apply_radial_burst_to_particles` (matches legacy's post-integration position perturbation).\n\nWhat the decomposition unlocks:\n- Pattern math is JSON-editable WGSL: add an 8th pattern by appending a `case` to the seed_pattern shader switch. AI agents can author novel seed shapes.\n- Each integrator stage (sample, noise, anti-clump, euler, wrap, inject) is a separate atom — swap Euler for Verlet (future sibling atom), or insert a new force-field contribution by adding another per-particle force atom before euler.\n- `simplex_noise_force_at_particles` and `anti_clump_particles` both accept any scalar Texture2D as their modulator — density (FluidSim), audio amplitude, masks, depth maps — so the same atoms compose into any particle sim, not just fluid.\n- The radial-burst impulse, gradient, and rotation are reusable building blocks for any future flow-field particle sim.",
